<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN364-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. avaṉaik kūkaikkōḻiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN364">
<l>vāṭā mālai pāṭiṉi yaṇiyap</l>
<l>pāṇaṉ ceṉṉik kēṇi pūvā</l>
<l>verimaru ṭāmaraip perumalar tayaṅka</l>
<l>maiviṭai yirumpōttuc centīc cērttik</l>
<l>kāyaṅ kaṉinta kaṇṇakaṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>naṟavuṇ cevvāy nāttiṟam peyarppa</l>
<l>vuṇṭun tiṉṟu mirappōrk kīntu</l>
<l>makiḻkam vammō maṟampō rōyē</l>
<l>yariya vākalu muriya peruma</l>
<l>nilampaka vīḻnta valaṅkaṟ palvēr</l>
<l>mutumarap pottiṟ katumeṉa viyampuṅ</l>
<l>kūkaik kōḻi yāṉāt</l>
<l>tāḻiya peruṅkā ṭeytiya ñāṉṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>While unfading garlands adorn the songstresses (1),</l>
<l>while big blossoms of flame-like lotus</l>
<l>that did not bloom in wells sway on the heads of the bards (2f.)</l>
<l corresp="4">putting a big male black ram on the red fire, </l>
<l corresp="6">while moving on the tongues of [our] toddy-drinking red mouths </l>
<l corresp="5">fat pieces large in extent that melt with spices, </l>
<l corresp="7">eating, feasting [and] giving to those who beg </l>
<l corresp="8">let us make merry, come, you of valorous battle! </l>
<l corresp="9">[Such things] are rightful, great man, as soon they will become difficult </l>
<l corresp="13">– at the time when we reach the big cremation ground with urns </l>
<l corresp="12">where the fowl [that is the] owls do not stop </l>
<l corresp="11">that give sound harshly from the hollows of old trees </l>
<l corresp="10">with many swaying roots that descend so that the ground is split. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
